show.description: For one hour every two weeks, DJ Schwippschwager and changing guests play their favourite game soundtracks across decades and platforms. Want to be a guest on the show? HMU @ lillul666@gmail.com

description: Being back in the studio for the first time since the lockdown this episode featured not one but two guests! DJ Nodding Trainride started the show with a diverse genre mix from games such as Silent Hill and PaRappa The Rapper. Around 29 minutes in, DJ State took over with his disco driven set including games like the Sims and Rollercoaster Tycoon 3. After the first hour DJ Schwippschwager played Drum ‘n’ Bass and low bitrate tunes from the Killer Instinct series and Mega Man 8 just to name a few.

description: Time feels different lately, accelerated in tranquility. All days looking like twins, forming alignments of strange repetitions, going on and on and on. I tried to bring some of that into the set, circling around some classics, mixed with a few dancy tracks, strange tunes and soothing melodies. I hope y’all enjoy the journey. Take good care of your mind and body, fill em with serenity and affection. Stay cool! :)

description:
uebelst am viben is the first musical encounter of LN(x) and OGGY OG. In the beginning we had 5 hours of DJing madness, which were sliced up into easily consumable pieces. Part one features many of our favourite breakbeat and electro tracks. Part two lies on the faster end of our musical spectrum. The focus of that part is juke, footwork and jungle but it ends with some dreamy tracks to fade yourself into sweet rest. Take your time and enjoy.

title: Radio Rasclat presents: Fruity Loup
description: Seit ich meinen ersten iPod bekam, lief er immer auf Shuffle Mode. Irgendwann hatte ich um die 4000 Tracks drauf. CD’s ausgeliehen, gebrannt und auf den iPod geladen, irgendwann die ganz besonderen Sachen auch mal gekauft. Ich habe Erinnerungen an Zugfahrten, Partys, kleine nächtliche Gehwegtänze, Freunde, die in meinem Zimmer chillen. Der iPod lief immer. Wiederentdeckungen von vergessener Musik, oder das tausendfache Hören eines Lieblingstracks.  Ich möchte euch die Musik zeigen, die in mir Gefühle auslöst. Lasst euch auf den Shuffle ein.
